</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR24:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR24"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              24-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 24</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 77</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Rosie the Riveter Day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">May 29, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 24, Alvarado-Gil.
                          Rosie the Riveter Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize the day of March 21, 2025, as Rosie the Riveter Day.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_0910FA88-C416-4CEA-B6F6-FBF922A1145C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Rosie the Riveter Day is celebrated on March 21 each year in honor of the cultural icon that represented the hardworking women who supported the American war effort during World War II; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E1F8018C-5E7D-4301-95D7-60AC78176FBA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Rosie the Riveter symbolized the millions of women who entered the workforce to replace male workers who were fighting in the war; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B6879621-2209-4476-9EC7-EA342056F020"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These women worked in factories and shipyards, building airplanes, tanks, and other supplies that were essential to the war effort, and their contributions not only helped win the war but also paved the way for women’s rights and opportunities in the workplace; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_073E8583-EE96-42AF-996A-E5C3983A9E67"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Rosie the Riveter Day celebrates the courage, strength, and determination of these women and serves as a reminder of their important role in American history; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_DFC66542-4FE5-400B-AAC5-144D61EF0EDA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature recognizes the day of March 21, 2025, as Rosie the Riveter Day to encourage people to recognize and honor the achievements of women in the workforce and to continue to promote gender equality and women’s empowerment; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B66CD9CB-C158-4D74-9746-5DB1E4790375"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
